reviews:
Front pockets are large, back pockets are just details - not pockets.
Material is thick enough to not cling, and comfortable overall.

I purchased these is a size 12, and they fit fairly true to size. The material is thick enough to not show lines, or feel like it's clinging to you.
There are no back pockets, only back pocket details.
But the best part of these shorts are the front pockets.
Actual. Functional. Pockets.
I can comfortably fit my phone in that front pocket. It's freeing to be able to use my hands again.
Easy to clean, baby and seat stay unstained. 9/10, would recommend.

I love this water bottle. I received the 40oz as a gift, and purchased the smaller one for my child.
It keeps drinks cold for a long time, and is light enough to carry in his backpack, despite being metal.

Bibs did their job, and helped keep moisture off baby's clothes from clothes.
However my baby ended up having a reaction to the backing, which is unfortunate.

Some of these magnets are stronger than others. They are used only to hold up paper, but there have been several instances where I brush up against my fridge and the paper and magnets fall to the floor.
I purchased these for my husband, they're his favourite warm socks. He works outside and needs a warm sock in those steel toes!

Alright y'all this thing is great.
It comes fully assembled. It has snaps to fold it up so you can easily store it. Lots of spots for hanging toys. The bars are also attached by snaps.
My only complaint is the music the sun plays is sort of tinny, and I don't recognize the tunes but hey. Neither does the baby.

Product fits a little small, but seems to be pretty close! I think if I'd purchased the next size up they'd be too big.
Overall a good product, I'm happy with what I got for the price.
It takes up a small amount of space, is easy to clean and holds a surprising amount!

Fits perfectly on my UppaBaby Vista bassinet attachment. I love that it zips up the front for easy access to baby, and the toggle to keep it up of it stops raining.
So easy to use!

It smells great, cleans well, and didn't appear to irritate my baby.
I love this brand for my kiddos.

My baby stays toasty in this sleep sack. I love the double zipper feature, and that it can be unzipped from the bottom.
There are snaps under the armpits to make arm holes smaller, so babies likely won't be able to pull their arms inside.
I wish the velcro was a little stronger, though. Baby is still in a bassinet, so being able to fold the excess on the bottom was a definite plus for this sleep sack. But it comes loose, so I don't bother with it anymore. Maybe snaps would have been a better idea?
Either way, it's a great product, and I will consider buying more.
My son loves all the stories, and they have a positive message. I love being to read these to him, just like my parents read them to.
Hat is comfy, and warm. It fits a little on the small side.

Arrived quickly and as expected. Started a blanket years ago, and couldn't locate this particular colour in store.
The quality has remained consistent.
This dino was a hit with my child. It seems to be well made. It was a little larger than I expected

I've had the case for nearly 2 years, and it doesn't seem to have held up as well as previous Otter Box cases.
The dust cover for the charging port has become difficult to move, I have to dig it out when inwant to charge my device. The bottom corners of the rubber cover never quite fit in the grooves properly.
I'm not a hugr fan of the huge cutout on the back, but based on rear button/camera position there's not a whole lot that could have been done differently.
That being said, I have dropped my pjone from varying heights onto many hard surfaces, and I have had a bus drive through a huge puddle and soak me while the phone was in my hand; my phone still works great, and looks new.

Works well, my teeth feel very clean.
The vibration for the 2 minute mark was alarming. I just assumed the toothbrush would turn off, instead it is a series of vibrations.
My 3 year old loves this game. It has increased his interest in learning numbers, and has helped teach him how to write numbers.
My Husband raves about these socks. He works outside, and his feet get wet from snow/rain, but they stay warm.

I bought these gloves for my Husband, but have used them myself several times.
They are extremely warm, and have kept my fingers warm while pulling my child in a wagon. I'm always pleasantly surprised when my fingers stay warm in gloves.
I bought the large size for my husband, and they fit him well. I'm am considering buying a smaller size for myself!

review_title: My baby digs this toy. The snap is too ...
reviews: My baby digs this toy. The snap is too small to fit over the car seat bar/handle, but we hang it elsewhere for him to grab and chew. He especially enjoys the squeaker inside.

review_title: I am very happy with this monitor
reviews:
I am very happy with this monitor.
Easy to use, I find it very sensitive to sound which is something I like. Even in the low light black and white mode I can see whether baby's eyes are open or closed.
Camera can be mounted to the wall, to get the best angle.
The two way speaker is nice, though I find my voice to be a tad spooky when I talk through the parent unit. I swear my voice isn't normally spooky.
Baby doesn't seem bothered by the voice though, so I guess it can't be all that bad.
A+, would buy again.
